    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="20"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                <head>20. National Security Decision Memorandum 77<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d20fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, Box 363, Subject Files, <gloss target="#t_NSDM1"
                            >NSDM</gloss>s 51–96. Secret; Sensitive. A copy was sent to the Chairman
                        of the Joint Chiefs of Staff.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-08-12">August 12, 1970</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Air Activity in Southeast Asia Over FY 71</item>
                </list>
                <p>Following the <gloss target="#t_VSSG1">VSSG</gloss> review,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d20fn2">See <ref target="#d13fn2">footnote 2, Document
                        13</ref>.</note> the President has directed that the Department of Defense
                    shall: <pb facs="0080" n="41" xml:id="pg_41"/>
                    <list>
                        <item>—Provide funding adequate to support an FY 1971 air activity level of
                            14,000 tactical air (<gloss target="#t_USAF1">USAF</gloss>, <gloss
                                target="#t_USN1">USN</gloss> and USMC), 1,000 B–52, and 1,000
                            gunship sorties monthly in Southeast Asia.</item>
                        <item>—Authorize a lower sorties level than funded—between 10,000 and 14,000
                            tactical air sorties flown monthly in Southeast Asia—depending upon
                            circumstances as determined by <gloss target="#t_COMUSMACV1"
                                >COMUSMACV</gloss>.</item>
                        <item>—Plan to compensate for this reduction in U.S. air activity by
                            continuing <gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss>’s intensive effort to
                            enhance the capabilities of the VNAF to at least 4,300 sorties monthly
                            and of the <gloss target="#t_RLAF1">RLAF</gloss> to 2,000 sorties
                            monthly during FY 71.</item>
                        <item>—Plan to close two bases in South Vietnam (Chu Lai and Tuy Hoa) during
                            FY 1971 and to place one base in Thailand (Takhli) on a caretaker basis
                            until a further review.</item>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">
                                    <hi rend="strong">Henry A. Kissinger</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
